Description: Sherd of East Greek pottery lid or possibly dish with flat-faced rim; orange-buff clay with many inclusions and mica; row of regularly set holes through rim, made before firing. Glazed fired orange-brown: three bands on rim, six on underside and one at centre of upper surface.
Curator's comments: Typologically close to 1965,0930.520, but in a different clay.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.537)
